<br>
i was wondering if the 50+ fire pets continue to use the fire elemental aura buff on themselves or if they just use the doofy o'kiels embers ds.<br>
<br>
reason being that we were in CoM the other night to take out rak ashir. the mage was foing to use the lower 50+ fire pet (highest one she had) but i decided it would be better to use the lvl 49 fire pet instead because fire elemental aura &gt; o'kiels embers &amp; the mini-wizzy just chain casts spells which rak would just resist every time... so bigger ds and actual mele...<br>
<br>
turned out the mage only had the 44 version of the fire pet /bonk but we still used it (since the shaman there was on the last step of her epic) and killed rak. at one point the pet almost bit the dust but a pally dove in with LoH... everyone was healing quite a bit and i was chain casting rune 3. near the end a rogue jumped in and landed a few backstabs until she was hit by the ae. (could run in when he casted spells) and the ranger there used trueshot which helped nicely. we barely did it but supposedly the 49 pets are way better than the 44 ones...<br>
<br>
also i read the post about the new resists messing up this fight, and the 44 pet was never hit by the ae so i immagine they are still immune. i doubt we could have outhealed that damage on that pet. this was a few days ago maby last week i forget... but the new resists were definately in because i remember everyone talking about it. (its a huge thing on a pvp server hehe)<br>
<br>
the higher level pet would have gotten hit less and if it uses the fire elemental aura the ds would have eaten up raks hp alot faster so just wondering mostly on that point if i made the right decision. i figured the ds would be doing most of the damage.<br>
<br>
for next time, any help appreciated. <p><center> <img src=http://www.homestead.com/veloxlupuspics/files/current_sig.jpg> <br>
